HEADWORD: Solely
<hw>Sole"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Singly; alone; only;
without another; <as>as, to rest a cause <ex>solely</ex> one argument;
to rely <ex>solely</ex>n one's own strength</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

